; Regression test for issue #771: --explicit not working without pre-declarations
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/771
;
; --explicit is now a no-op; --strict alone warns about undeclared accounts
; and commodities regardless of whether any account directives exist.

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

test bal --strict
             $-10.00  Assets:Cash
              $10.00  Expenses:Food
--------------------
                   0
__ERROR__
Warning: "$FILE", line 8: Unknown account 'Expenses:Food'
Warning: "$FILE", line 8: Unknown commodity '$'
Warning: "$FILE", line 9: Unknown account 'Assets:Cash'
end test

; --explicit --strict with cleared transaction should still warn
test bal --explicit --strict
             $-10.00  Assets:Cash
              $10.00  Expenses:Food
--------------------
                   0
__ERROR__
Warning: "$FILE", line 8: Unknown account 'Expenses:Food'
Warning: "$FILE", line 8: Unknown commodity '$'
Warning: "$FILE", line 9: Unknown account 'Assets:Cash'
end test

; --pedantic should error on the first unknown account
test bal --pedantic -> 1
__ERROR__
While parsing file "$FILE", line 8:
While parsing posting:
  Expenses:Food    $10.00

Error: Unknown account 'Expenses:Food'
end test
